name: Nav Athwal
tweet: Bold Prediction: In 10 years, VC Firms run by non-founders will start to become obsolete. Capital and pattern recognition will be insufficient to sustain deal flow as founders place greater importance on operating experience among their investors and board #founders

name: Nav Athwal
tweet: True success is achieving one’s goals while remaining humble. Humility is far too undervalued and often times in business large egos leave little room for it. #founders

name: Nav Athwal
tweet: Optimize for building a good business rather than the next round of financing.  Celebrate selling customers on your product rather than VC's. #founders

name: Nav Athwal
tweet: Good Co-Founders are critical...bad ones can be fatal. Best Co-Founder Pairing = CEO + CTO; Worst = MBA 1 + MBA 2. The less overlap of skills the better. True value is having someone in the trenches w/you for mental support. Someone who gets it as much as you do.
